.Dd May 7, 2026
.Dt MOXY-RESTART 7
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm moxy-restart
.Nd the
.Li restart
meta tool, and the Claude Code system-prompt limitation
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Xr moxy 1
injects a
.Li restart
meta tool into the unified MCP server.
Calling
.Li restart{server: "<name>"}
restarts a configured child by name:
.Bl -bullet -offset indent -compact
.It
For persistent subprocess servers, closes and re-spawns the process.
.It
For ephemeral servers, re-probes capabilities.
.It
For
.Xr moxin 7
(native) servers, re-discovers the moxin's TOML from
.Ev MOXIN_PATH
and rebuilds the in-process server.
.El
.Pp
After every successful restart,
.Nm moxy
emits a JSON-RPC
.Li notifications/tools/list_changed
notification on every open SSE stream, per the MCP spec
.Pq 2025-11-25 .
.Pp
The tool is annotated with
.Li destructiveHint: true
so MCP clients that surface annotations
.Pq Claude Code does
prompt the user before each invocation.
.Sh CLAUDE CODE LIMITATION
.Ss Symptom
After a successful
.Li restart ,
moxy's runtime tool registry reflects the new tool surface and
.Li tools/call
dispatches correctly.
The Claude Code session's system-prompt tool list, however,
.Em does not change ,
even across new user turns within the same session.
Tool descriptions, additions, and removals are invisible to the model
until the user takes one of the workarounds below.
.Ss What does refresh
.Bl -tag -width "/mcp \(-> Reconnect"
.It Restart the Claude Code session entirely
Boot reads
.Li tools/list
fresh and rebuilds the system prompt.
.It Li /mcp \(-> Reconnect
The
.Li /mcp
slash command exposes a per-server reconnect action that tears down and
re-establishes the MCP client connection.
This triggers a fresh
.Li initialize
plus
.Li tools/list ,
and propagates the result into the active conversation's tool surface
.Em and
system prompt.
This is the recommended workflow after calling moxy's
.Li restart .
.El
.Ss What does not refresh
.Bl -tag -width "list_changed"
.It Li notifications/tools/list_changed
Claude Code's MCP SDK layer parses the notification and refreshes its
internal cache, but the active conversation's tool surface is captured
in a closure at session start and is not propagated when the cache
updates.
This is an upstream Claude Code bug, not a moxy bug.
.El
.Ss Recommended workflow
.Bl -enum -compact
.It
Call
.Li restart{server: "<name>"}
to reload the moxin or re-spawn the subprocess child.
.It
Run
.Li /mcp
in the Claude Code TUI.
.It
Select the moxy entry, then choose
.Em Reconnect .
.El
.Pp
After this, the model's tool surface reflects the post-restart state.
.Sh UPSTREAM REFERENCES
.Bl -tag -width "anthropics/claude-code#XXXXX" -compact
.It anthropics/claude-code#4118
Original feature request
.Pq open since 2025-07 ;
partial fix in 2.1.0 advertised in CHANGELOG; community follow-up
confirms the active-conversation propagation is still missing.
.It anthropics/claude-code#50515
Same-server A/B confirming
.Li resources/list_changed
works while
.Li tools/list_changed
is dropped on stdio MCP, with
.Li v2.1.113
repro.
.It anthropics/claude-code#50339
Bytecode-level walkthrough of the gated SDK handler in Claude Desktop
.Pq directMcpHost.js
showing why the notification never propagates.
.It anthropics/claude-code#51507
Stdio MCP process recycling regression in
.Li v2.1.107+ ,
which is a separate issue moxy users may also encounter.
.El
.Sh MOXY-SIDE VERIFICATION
The notification is exercised in
.Li internal/proxy/proxy_test.go
.Pq TestRestartMoxinSwapsChildAndNotifies
and
.Li zz-tests_bats/streamable_http.bats
.Pq sse_receives_list_changed_after_restart .
A standalone POC
.Pa zz-pocs/list-changed/serve.ts
isolates the wire-level behavior from moxy.
